  "framing": "Leakage-free pseudo-prospective: V0/V1/V2 tiled-ETAS variants fit once at cutoff0, reconditioned forward weekly. At each window the convex stacking weights are fit on the STRICTLY-PAST 7-day Poisson log-score (expanding holdout) and shrunk to the V0 anchor; the scored window is OUT-OF-SAMPLE (its IGPE vs base may be + or -). IGPE(stack vs base V0) scored at 7d (product) and 30d. gate_7d_global reports the GLOBAL-view paired-T CI, W p-value and positive-window fraction the pre-registered ship rule consumes (criteria b/c/d); the full rule also needs >=2 regional views (not covered by this global run). If the global criteria are not met, E12 is recorded as a dead-end (a valid result)."
